  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 336
    Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Old Age
---
Up to one’s last breath, one may retain the simple joys of childhood, the
poetic ecstasies of the young man, the enthusiasms of maturity. Right to
the end, one may intoxicate one’s spirit with flowers, with beauty and with
smiles.
